HB 206 Original 2026 Regular Session Green
Abstract: Provides for the authority of legislators to attend any meeting held by any state
board, commission, agency, authority, task force, or committee and specifies that this
authority also extends to any entity with membership subject to legislative
confirmation.
Present law authorizes members of the legislature to attend any meeting of any state board,
commission, agency, or committee. Further provides that this attendance extends to both
public meetings and those held in private or executive session.
Proposed law retains present law and provides that the authority of members of the
legislature to attend any meeting extends to meetings held by a task force or authority.
Further provides that the authority of members of the legislature to attend any meeting
applies to any entity if any or all of its membership is subject to legislative confirmation.
(Amends R.S. 24:8)
